Compared to the world, the situation in the Czech Republic is not improving at all.
According to the World Bank the Czech Republic is in 74th place in terms of conditions for the company, i.e. 8 more places compared to last year.
The Absurdity of the Year competition was first introduced in 2006 and continues each year under the same scenario.
Anyone can report administrative and bureaucratic absurdities every year from April to the end of September, which is the final deadline for the closing of the competition.
