Czech children get drunk with rum and fernet. Beer is no longer fashionable and acts softly.
Fernet, rum, vodka and exceptionally also the best whisky brand are stolen from parents.
These are drinks that most often bring those who get drunk, who are not yet fifteen years old, into the hands of the doctor.
Children who are treated in hospital for re-offending are no exception.
This is the result of the experience of doctors who encounter cases similar to admissions from the children's departments of hospitals.
