"It's usually rum or fernet."
"Today it's fashionable alcohol, especially in elementary schools."
"In some cases, it was slivovice that they brought back from the house," added Jurinova.
According to the Head of Department Pelikan, seeing drunk children between the ages of 13 and 14 in hospital admissions is a normal phenomenon.
