Only cases with acute intoxication requiring hospitalization are included in statistics.
Intoxicated children who are after emergency care taken home by parents or the police are not counted.
In addition to the cases of children who sit and drink a bottle of alcohol after school, according to Pelikan he exsites three seasonal waves with which one can count: the day of witches, the saint Sylvestre and the end of the school year.
