It is not clear whether Mrs Fernández wants to remain in politics beyond the end of her term of office, now that her husband is no longer with her.
If she does, she needs to gain support from the middle class, among whom Kirchnerism is highly advocated.
When the Argentinians return from their summer holidays in March, the wave of sympathy for her will have refluted.
If she wants to win another election, she will have to decide whether to repudiate many of her husband’s policies without any noise.
