The situation of young people on the labour market has deteriorated further, with a further increase in the unemployment rate, rising to 24.2% in metropolitan France (+ 0.9 point over three months, +0.5 point over one year) and 25% including the overseas departments.
In the third quarter, 637,000 young people aged 15-24 were unemployed within the meaning of the ILO.
Seniors experienced a slight increase in unemployment, to 6.4% in metropolitan France (+0.2 points over three months as well as over one year), i.e. 482,000 people aged 50 or over, and 6.6% with the French overseas departments.
Only 25-49 year-olds benefited from stable unemployment in the third quarter, at 8.3% in metropolitan France (-0.1 point over three months, +0.1 point over one year) and 8.8% throughout France.
